Welcome to the Red Stag Inn.  How can I be of service to ye?
Looking for a Drink?  Some Food?  Maybe a room?

The Druids are all up in arms again.  Rumour is, they think something's goin on in the caverns under the mountain. They're even payen gold for folks to go and have a look.  Must be bad times they're on if they handen out metal tae folks. *Wipes down the bar*
Mitchan's havin' a hell of a time with xvart raids again.  Ever since they moved out from the hills to the north they just won't leave his farm be.

Bandits are acting up again.  Hear there making camps to the south west and robben folks on the road if the hear coins jingle.  If you talk to High Constable Keegan up in Caer Corwell he can tell you more.
*Wipes out an empty glass and readjusts a jar with a "Tips" label on it*
Just up the road. North Gate. Head west, yer cant miss it he's in the main keep of the Caer. Just.. mind yer manners with him. A bit of a... particular sort, he is.
*Wipes out an empty glass and readjusts a jar with a "Tips" label on it*

Ah, mind those xvarts, they can smart. Best to bring a group with ye if ye can. But, if ye want to get to Mitchan's farm, take the south west gate out o' town and start on the road leading south.  Keep straight on that path through the farms outside o' town. Once you get to the forest yer in the right spot, take the road east you can't miss it.

Just head out the North Gate like yer going to Caer Corwell, but instead o' taken the path that branches west toward the Caer, you want to head up the hill to the east.
